00:12:19.238 --> 00:12:22.283
<i>Pinche </i>urban white whale.
You and these fucking ghosts.

232
00:12:22.366 --> 00:12:24.660
Not ghosts. Cruz.
they're very fucking real.

233
00:12:24.744 --> 00:12:27.705
See how scared that dude was
when you walked in with the two?

234
00:12:27.788 --> 00:12:31.208
Motherfucking Clippers. man.
Straight ass cheeks. cuh.

235
00:12:31.292 --> 00:12:34.086
[Choi] How do you move with all
those bookies' hands in your pocket. bro?

236
00:12:34.170 --> 00:12:37.047
Jealous men shouldn't pimp women.
and broke niggas shouldn't gamble.

237
00:12:37.131 --> 00:12:38.466
[laughing]

238
00:12:38.549 --> 00:12:40.718
-Fuck out of here. cuh.
-Let me see that.

239
00:12:42.052 --> 00:12:43.262
You stupid motherfucker.

240
00:12:43.345 --> 00:12:44.847
-Ya couldn't help yourself.
-What?

241
00:12:44.930 --> 00:12:47.683
Your baby uncle
stole that watch from the Halloween job.

242
00:12:48.476 --> 00:12:51.729
Oh. Oh. this?
I figure I haven't sold it yet.

243
00:12:51.812 --> 00:12:54.315
Might as well floss this motherfucker
and get some bitches.

244
00:12:54.398 --> 00:12:57.818
-Ain't you got enough bitches. bro?
-[Coltrane] You must have got me confused.

245
00:12:57.902 --> 00:12:59.153
My name may be Coltrane.

246
00:12:59.236 --> 00:13:01.989
but I do not play improvisational shit
when it comes to jobs.

247
00:13:02.072 --> 00:13:04.325
-You do it again. you're done.
-[Deon] . Man. fuck that.

248
00:13:04.408 --> 00:13:06.786
You may be in charge.
but we all contribute to this crew.

249
00:13:06.869 --> 00:13:09.872
Last job we pulled was in March.
It's fucking November. nigga.

250
00:13:09.955 --> 00:13:12.792
Now. I may not be as educated as you.
but I know math.

251
00:13:12.875 --> 00:13:17.505
And right now. I got one. two.
three. four. five. six mouths to feed.

252
00:13:17.588 --> 00:13:21.091
Plus half my mama's bills.
minus seven months of this bullshit.

253
00:13:21.175 --> 00:13:22.301
You know what that equals?

254
00:13:22.384 --> 00:13:24.428
A broke motherfucker
who can't even get his gamble on.

255
00:13:24.512 --> 00:13:26.639
'Trane knows we behind schedule.
but we need to chill.

256
00:13:26.722 --> 00:13:29.183
Nah. fuck that. nephew.
Chill don't pay the bills.

257
00:13:29.266 --> 00:13:31.018
We all know why we ain't been working.

258
00:13:31.101 --> 00:13:34.438
And you know what. I get it. You was going
through some real personal shit.

259
00:13:34.522 --> 00:13:38.234
What I'm not about to do is let no nigga
tell me how to eat when I'm starving.

260
00:13:38.317 --> 00:13:39.360
This nigga owes us.

261
00:13:40.319 --> 00:13:42.238
He speaking for all of you?

262
00:13:42.321 --> 00:13:44.240
[tense music playing]

263
00:13:44.323 --> 00:13:46.158
Deon's not wrong. 'Trane.

264
00:13:47.535 --> 00:13:49.745
A'ight. now it's on you to make us whole.

265
00:13:50.287 --> 00:13:52.915
We need two more jobs
in the next two months.

266
00:13:55.251 --> 00:13:57.711
-Don't fucking sell that watch.
-Nigga. I know!

267
00:13:57.795 --> 00:14:00.714
Fuck it. shit.
just give me my cut from Halloween.

268
00:14:01.507 --> 00:14:04.885
This nigga mad. [scoffs]

269
00:14:04.969 --> 00:14:07.763
-[Choi] Why you always doing dumb shit?
-[Deon] What you talking about?

270
00:14:07.847 --> 00:14:10.432
-[Choi] Let me see that shit.
-[Deon] You just mad because… Look.

271
00:14:10.516 --> 00:14:11.851
This shit nice. right?

272
00:14:29.451 --> 00:14:30.452
[sighs]

273
00:14:33.998 --> 00:14:36.000
[melancholy music playing]

274
00:14:37.251 --> 00:14:38.836
[sniffs]

275
00:14:42.923 --> 00:14:45.551
[gunshots echoing]

276
00:14:45.634 --> 00:14:46.927
[Stiles] <i>Manny. you got him?</i>

277
00:14:47.011 --> 00:14:49.805
-[man gasping and groaning]
-[dramatic music playing]

278
00:14:49.889 --> 00:14:53.309
This is 1K20. Officer down.
Officer needs help.

279
00:14:53.392 --> 00:14:54.894
-[Manny breathes shakily]
-God!

280
00:14:56.520 --> 00:14:57.855
[voice breaking] Come on. man.

281
00:15:00.190 --> 00:15:02.860
Please. Come on. man. Manny!

282
00:15:05.696 --> 00:15:06.530
[Sealy] Stiles!

283
00:15:06.614 --> 00:15:07.698
[music fades]

284
00:15:09.199 --> 00:15:10.784
Heard you got the Alvarez girl.

285
00:15:10.868 --> 00:15:12.536
Great work. Isaiah.

286
00:15:12.620 --> 00:15:14.413
I know how
these motherfuckers think. Jimmy.

287
00:15:14.496 --> 00:15:17.458
Growing up where you did. how you did.
that makes you good police.

288
00:15:17.541 --> 00:15:18.375
Yeah.

289
00:15:18.459 --> 00:15:20.836
Make you a great captain
when I retire at the end of the year.

290
00:15:20.920 --> 00:15:24.381
But that secret board you got
behind your desk ain't helping the cause.

291
00:15:25.674 --> 00:15:27.092
-Viggiano's case.
-Oh.

292
00:15:27.176 --> 00:15:29.345
The Beverly Hills robbery.
It fits the pattern.

293
00:15:29.428 --> 00:15:31.972
We've been through this before. Isaiah.
There's no pattern.

294
00:15:32.056 --> 00:15:34.350
No pattern is the pattern. Jimmy.

295
00:15:34.433 --> 00:15:36.477
Four perps. at least two of them Black.

296
00:15:36.560 --> 00:15:38.395
They hit high-end. high-level targets.

297
00:15:38.479 --> 00:15:40.606
changing their MO every time
so we don't connect them.

298
00:15:40.689 --> 00:15:43.108
I thought you said
they always use some kind of diversion.

299
00:15:43.192 --> 00:15:46.278
Last night was the diversion.
Halloween in Los Angeles?

300
00:15:46.362 --> 00:15:49.782
Parties. parades. crowd control?
No bigger diversion than that.

301
00:15:49.865 --> 00:15:51.241
It fits the pattern.

302
00:15:51.325 --> 00:15:53.953
But nothing's matched
your supposed pattern for seven months.

303
00:15:54.036 --> 00:15:55.788
-It stopped cold.
-I think we were wrong.

304
00:15:55.871 --> 00:15:57.748
I just don't understand
why they needed four guys

305
00:15:57.831 --> 00:15:59.458
to steal a quarter-million-dollar watch.

306
00:15:59.541 --> 00:16:02.211
-Something's off. Shit's different.
-A different crew entirely. maybe?

307
00:16:03.253 --> 00:16:04.713
Come on. Jimmy.

308
00:16:05.297 --> 00:16:08.133
Hey. give me the Beverly Hills case.
Put Viggiano on ice.

309
00:16:08.217 --> 00:16:10.177
You need to let Vig work his case.

310
00:16:11.220 --> 00:16:12.972
Focus on your career.

311
00:16:13.514 --> 00:16:15.557
You got phenomenal instincts.

312
00:16:15.641 --> 00:16:18.560
-As captain. you--
-I don't want that shit. Jimmy.

313
00:16:19.353 --> 00:16:20.854
I wanna bring these guys in.

314
00:16:21.730 --> 00:16:24.316
-I can't do that stuck behind a desk.
-But what does Candace want?

315
00:16:26.485 --> 00:16:28.404
Aren't you supposed
to be having dinner with her?

316
00:16:29.863 --> 00:16:31.156
Oh. fuck.

317
00:16:33.075 --> 00:16:33.951
Yeah.

318
00:16:34.952 --> 00:16:36.912
[tires screech]

319
00:16:39.665 --> 00:16:42.126
["Rain" playing]

320
00:16:47.464 --> 00:16:53.178
<i>♪ Sometimes it's soft as a misty rain… ♪</i>

321
00:16:53.262 --> 00:16:55.723
-[Candace] Try harder. my ass.
-[door unlocks]

322
00:16:59.184 --> 00:17:02.104
I should've robbed a bank.
You'd have been here faster.

323
00:17:02.187 --> 00:17:04.648
Made your favorite.
but not sure if it's still any good.

324
00:17:04.732 --> 00:17:07.943
Lost track of time. baby.
You know what? I'm here now.

325
00:17:08.027 --> 00:17:10.195
-[chuckles]
-Mm. Yay. How was work?

326
00:17:11.113 --> 00:17:12.364
Oh. um…

327
00:17:14.283 --> 00:17:16.535
-You don't wanna talk about my work.
-No.

328
00:17:16.618 --> 00:17:19.496
Actually. you don't wanna talk about work.

329
00:17:19.580 --> 00:17:23.375
But since it's all you think about.
there's nothing for us to talk about.

330
00:17:26.503 --> 00:17:28.130
Okay. Uh…

331
00:17:29.965 --> 00:17:31.383
Nine-year-old girl.

332
00:17:31.467 --> 00:17:33.385
Paola Alvarez.

333
00:17:33.469 --> 00:17:36.180
Kidnapped by some Armenian crash dummies.

334
00:17:36.263 --> 00:17:38.891
Held hostage in a house in Hollywood.

335
00:17:38.974 --> 00:17:40.392
I get into the house.

336
00:17:40.476 --> 00:17:43.645
I. uh. disable the first guy.

337
00:17:44.146 --> 00:17:46.231
Second dude wants to play games.

338
00:17:46.732 --> 00:17:50.360
-Tried to get him to make the right call…
-Oh. babe. Isaiah.

339
00:17:51.111 --> 00:17:53.072
[sighs] I'm so sorry.

340
00:17:54.073 --> 00:17:55.115
Oh…

341
00:17:55.991 --> 00:17:59.119
You always want these men
to make different decisions.

342
00:17:59.661 --> 00:18:02.498
But not everybody's built like you. babe.

343
00:18:02.581 --> 00:18:05.459
The little girl. Paola.
she's back home with her father.

344
00:18:05.542 --> 00:18:09.797
Some big-time cartel guy. But. you know.
it's not her fault who her daddy is.

345
00:18:12.132 --> 00:18:14.551
How do you know that about her father.
but not about your own?

346
00:18:15.135 --> 00:18:16.720
His behavior's not your fault.

347
00:18:17.304 --> 00:18:19.306
But you can't help taking it on.

348
00:18:20.516 --> 00:18:23.685
Listen. Dr. Stiles.
this session's been great.

349
00:18:23.769 --> 00:18:26.688
but I can no longer afford the copay. so…

350
00:18:26.772 --> 00:18:30.109
You can't afford to keep treating our son
like your father treated you.

351
00:18:30.192 --> 00:18:31.318
I ain't like that nigga.

352
00:18:31.401 --> 00:18:34.404
Different reason to run the streets.
different reason to own a gun.

353
00:18:34.488 --> 00:18:35.614
Same working hours.

354
00:18:35.697 --> 00:18:37.991
Candace. I never lied to you
about who I am.

355
00:18:38.075 --> 00:18:39.284
-You had options.
-Oh boy.

356
00:18:39.368 --> 00:18:42.496
You could've picked the suit.
Could've been Mrs. Uptight Motherfucker.

357
00:18:42.579 --> 00:18:45.791
You and Malik aren't as different
from each other as you think.

358
00:18:45.874 --> 00:18:47.960
But back in college. I didn't want him.

359
00:18:48.544 --> 00:18:49.878
I wanted you.

360
00:18:51.797 --> 00:18:53.882
I want you.

361
00:18:55.050 --> 00:18:56.343
[scoffs]

362
00:18:56.426 --> 00:18:57.678
On time.

363
00:18:59.596 --> 00:19:00.430
Baby.

364
00:19:02.307 --> 00:19:05.144
We can keep having
the same conversation over and over.

365
00:19:05.227 --> 00:19:06.728
but it's never gonna go any different.

366
00:19:06.812 --> 00:19:08.605
Can we skip to the end already?

367
00:19:08.689 --> 00:19:11.608
Eat this incredible meal you prepared.

368
00:19:11.692 --> 00:19:13.026
Enjoy ourselves.

369
00:19:14.486 --> 00:19:15.571
Sure.

370
00:19:16.113 --> 00:19:17.489
It's getting late.

371
00:19:18.657 --> 00:19:20.284
-Let me heat up the chicken.
-Okay.

372
00:19:23.245 --> 00:19:24.621
I'll go wash up.

373
00:19:27.249 --> 00:19:29.334
Happy anniversary. by the way.

374
00:19:29.418 --> 00:19:31.837
["Welcome to My World" playing]

375
00:19:34.840 --> 00:19:35.674
[Stiles exhales]

376
00:19:47.978 --> 00:19:49.479
-[Coltrane] Hey.
-[Ebony] Hi.

377
00:19:49.563 --> 00:19:51.732
[Coltrane] Tonight.
I feel like celebrating.

378
00:19:51.815 --> 00:19:54.109
Cash take was 1.7 million.

379
00:19:55.110 --> 00:19:56.778
Wouldn't have happened without you.

380
00:19:56.862 --> 00:19:58.947
Everything went off without a hitch.

381
00:19:59.031 --> 00:20:00.616
All five of us.

382
00:20:00.699 --> 00:20:03.368
We got in. We got out. Clean.

383
00:20:04.244 --> 00:20:06.788
You were amazing last night.
You didn't miss a beat.

384
00:20:08.540 --> 00:20:11.001
Felt good being in the moment with you.

385
00:20:11.084 --> 00:20:12.794
Two of us. as a team again.

386
00:20:13.503 --> 00:20:14.880
Like we were before.

387
00:20:14.963 --> 00:20:18.342
Yeah. um. Coltrane. about last night.

388
00:20:20.302 --> 00:20:21.845
I can't do that again.

389
00:20:23.222 --> 00:20:24.848
I was terrified.

390
00:20:24.932 --> 00:20:26.808
When you didn't
come through the door on time…

391
00:20:26.892 --> 00:20:27.851
I was only seconds off.

392
00:20:27.935 --> 00:20:31.021
Exactly. and if you'd run
into a real problem. I just…

393
00:20:31.104 --> 00:20:32.773
But I didn't. And I won't.

394
00:20:32.856 --> 00:20:35.067
You can't promise me that.

395
00:20:38.695 --> 00:20:39.696
Look.

396
00:20:41.740 --> 00:20:42.866
[Ebony exhales]

397
00:20:43.992 --> 00:20:47.079
When we lost Zahir…

398
00:20:49.623 --> 00:20:51.333
something inside me changed.

399
00:20:53.543 --> 00:20:56.296
I just don't feel the way I used to feel.

400
00:20:58.757 --> 00:21:01.510
Look. I want you to think
about what we said.

401
00:21:02.219 --> 00:21:04.846
Remember we said we'd be out
once we had the baby?

402
00:21:04.930 --> 00:21:09.142
We'd live a normal life.
not looking over our shoulders anymore?

403
00:21:09.226 --> 00:21:10.894
That was our dream.

404
00:21:11.645 --> 00:21:12.521
[Coltrane] Mm-hmm.

405
00:21:13.647 --> 00:21:15.148
[sighs] We may not have our son.

406
00:21:15.232 --> 00:21:17.818
but I'm not willing to let go
of that part of the dream.

407
00:21:19.528 --> 00:21:20.821
Okay.

408
00:21:25.742 --> 00:21:27.369
The guys are hungry. Ebony.

409
00:21:28.161 --> 00:21:29.371
I have to make them whole.

410
00:21:29.454 --> 00:21:32.791
We had March. but last night was only
the second job that we had this year.

411
00:21:38.297 --> 00:21:40.841
Two more jobs. Two more jobs. that's it.

412
00:21:40.924 --> 00:21:43.260
You and I can focus
on our future together.

413
00:21:45.012 --> 00:21:46.263
Do you mean that?

414
00:21:48.598 --> 00:21:49.766
I love you. Ebony.

415
00:21:50.684 --> 00:21:51.852
I love you too.

416
00:21:54.813 --> 00:21:56.023
Come here.

417
00:21:58.900 --> 00:22:00.402
You're so beautiful.

418
00:22:01.486 --> 00:22:05.240
Do you wanna go upstairs
and work up an appetite?

419
00:22:06.325 --> 00:22:08.160
I thought you'd never ask.

420
00:22:09.494 --> 00:22:10.829
[Ebony laughs]

421
00:22:10.912 --> 00:22:12.289
["Ready" playing]

422
00:22:12.372 --> 00:22:15.584
<i>♪ I'm ready for something different ♪</i>

423
00:22:15.667 --> 00:22:17.669
<i>♪ Cleansing my system ♪</i>

424
00:22:19.546 --> 00:22:21.256
<i>♪ Tonight ♪</i>

425
00:22:23.425 --> 00:22:26.428
<i>♪ Thought it was the final</i>
<i>But it's the arrival ♪</i>

426
00:22:26.511 --> 00:22:29.514
<i>♪ Coming out the gate. with the wave</i>
<i>It's the tidal ♪</i>

427
00:22:29.598 --> 00:22:34.227
<i>♪ Feel like a revival</i>
<i>Coming from inside of me ♪</i>

428
00:22:40.275 --> 00:22:41.526
Candace. baby.

429
00:22:42.235 --> 00:22:43.612
This was delicious.

430
00:22:44.696 --> 00:22:48.325
Mm. Well. I only cook twice a year.
so I'm glad it was edible at least.

431
00:22:51.870 --> 00:22:54.998
Hey. we don't have
to clean up right away. You know?

432
00:22:56.625 --> 00:22:57.918
Good night. Isaiah.

433
00:22:58.543 --> 00:23:00.545
[poignant music playing]

434
00:23:01.129 --> 00:23:02.255
[sighs]

435
00:23:05.717 --> 00:23:06.927
[softly] All right.

436
00:23:14.101 --> 00:23:15.477
Good night. Candace.

437
00:23:36.748 --> 00:23:38.750
[poignant music continues]

438
00:23:57.018 --> 00:23:59.521
Oh. shit.

439
00:24:56.453 --> 00:24:58.455
[music turns melancholy]

440
00:25:25.357 --> 00:25:26.358
[music fades]

441
00:25:28.109 --> 00:25:30.570
-[gentle R&B music playing]
-[footsteps approaching]

442
00:25:32.572 --> 00:25:34.199
[Stiles] Breakfast is in the oven.

443
00:25:38.912 --> 00:25:39.996
Thanks. Dad.

444
00:25:41.373 --> 00:25:43.542
-Hey. grab mine too. yeah?
-Yeah.

445
00:25:45.710 --> 00:25:47.420
How was your game yesterday?

446
00:25:48.713 --> 00:25:49.756
It was cool.

447
00:25:50.465 --> 00:25:52.300
I had ten points.

448
00:25:53.510 --> 00:25:54.844
-Three rebounds.
-Okay.

449
00:25:54.928 --> 00:25:56.846
Five assists. though.

450
00:25:56.930 --> 00:25:58.265
And a steal.

451
00:25:58.348 --> 00:26:00.725
-Hey. good game. son.
-[chuckles]

452
00:26:00.809 --> 00:26:01.851
Yeah.

453
00:26:02.561 --> 00:26:06.731
Uh… would've been cool
if you had come through. though.

454
00:26:09.234 --> 00:26:12.028
[Stiles] I saw your next home game
on the calendar. I'll be there.

455
00:26:13.196 --> 00:26:14.281
Sure.

456
00:26:16.074 --> 00:26:17.617
I'm giving you my word.

457
00:26:18.159 --> 00:26:20.954
That shit means something. I'll be there.

458
00:26:22.956 --> 00:26:25.584
Noah. go get ready for school.

459
00:26:26.501 --> 00:26:28.753
-Can I…?
-Yeah.

460
00:26:30.088 --> 00:26:33.300
Oh. look at Mom with the drip. huh?

461
00:26:41.433 --> 00:26:42.726
Thanks for making breakfast.

462
00:26:42.809 --> 00:26:45.228
Yeah. my pancakes are better than yours.

463
00:26:45.312 --> 00:26:46.688
[snickers]

464
00:26:51.943 --> 00:26:55.322
I'm sorry. Isaiah. about last night.

465
00:26:56.197 --> 00:26:58.617
I wouldn't have taken that tone if…

466
00:26:59.618 --> 00:27:01.703
Why didn't you just tell me
you remembered?

467
00:27:02.704 --> 00:27:07.542
I had a different idea…
of how things would go.

468
00:27:09.419 --> 00:27:12.005
[exhales] I hate we're like this. I…

469
00:27:13.256 --> 00:27:15.342
-I hate it this way.
-I know.

470
00:27:19.679 --> 00:27:23.308
<i>♪ I can't imagine a world without you ♪</i>

471
00:27:23.892 --> 00:27:25.477
<i>♪ I just wanna love you… ♪</i>

472
00:27:25.560 --> 00:27:28.480
[Candace] Oh. Isaiah. wow.

473
00:27:32.025 --> 00:27:34.653
[both laugh]

474
00:27:35.570 --> 00:27:37.614
-[exhales]
-I miss this.

475
00:27:40.700 --> 00:27:42.202
-[cell phone buzzing]
-Babe…

476
00:27:46.164 --> 00:27:47.666
